[2;36m                    [0m         +        return new [1;35mZipArchiveThresholdInputStream[0m[1m([0mzipInput[1m)[0m;                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              [1m}[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              [35m/[0m**                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Patch [33mResult[0m===                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===[33mIssue[0m===                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mReport[0m===                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         # Evaluation Report                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ## Summary                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         The initial issue is a persistent libFuzzer timeout when exercising the POI-OOXML   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ZIP entry source. A patch was introduced in `ZipInputStreamZipEntrySource` to limit [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         the number of entries read from a ZIP stream by counting entries and comparing      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         against a maximum threshold obtained via `[1;35mZipSecureFile.getMaxFileCount[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m`. After   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         applying this change, the fuzzer still reports the same timeout error.              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ## Description                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m. Initial Issue                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Observed behavior: libFuzzer reports “ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout” while running [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         tests against the ZIP entry source implementation.                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - No further error output or stack trace is produced—only a timeout indication   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         from the fuzzer harness.                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m. Key Observations                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - The harness repeatedly invokes the ZIP parsing logic but does not itself crash [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         or raise an exception.                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Timeout suggests either extremely slow processing of certain inputs or a       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         potential infinite loop/blocking operation in the code handling the ZIP stream.     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - No partial logs indicate entry count or threshold checks triggered before the  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         timeout.                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m. Patch Attempt                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - File modified:                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              `poi-ooxml/src/main/java/org/apache/poi/openxml4j/util/ZipInputStreamZipEntryS [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ource.java`                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Changes introduced:                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              • Declaration of `long entryCount = [1;36m0[0m` and retrieval of `long maxCount` from   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `[1;35mZipSecureFile.getMaxFileCount[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m`.                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              • In the loop that reads `ZipArchiveEntry` objects, increment `entryCount` on  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         each entry.                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              • If `entryCount` exceeds `maxCount`, throw an `IllegalStateException` with a  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         formatted message.                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Patch diff snippet:                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              ```                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              public [1;35mZipInputStreamZipEntrySource[0m[1m([0mZipArchiveThresholdInputStream inp[1m)[0m throws [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         IOException [1m{[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                  final Set[1m<[0m[1;95mString[0m[39m> filenames = new HashSet<>[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         long entryCount = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         long maxCount = [0m[1;35mZipSecureFile.getMaxFileCount[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         for [0m[1;39m([0m[39m;;[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             final ZipArchiveEntry zipEntry = [0m[1;35minp.getNextEntry[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mzipEntry == null[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                 break;[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             entryCount++;[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mentryCount > maxCount[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                 throw new [0m[1;35mIllegalStateException[0m[1;39m([0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                     [0m[1;35mString.format[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"ZIP archive contains too many entries [0m[32m([0m[32m%d[0m[32m)[0m[32m, [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32mexceeding max of %d"[0m[39m,[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                                   entryCount, maxCount[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             String name = [0m[1;35mzipEntry.getName[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             [0m[33m...[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[33m...[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```  [0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Result After Patch  [0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Execution with libFuzzer still ends in a timeout:  [0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     “ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout”  [0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No change in fuzzer output beyond continued timeout—no new exceptions or early[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtermination due to the entry-count guard.  [0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Areas for Further Investigation  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The loop in `ZipInputStreamZipEntrySource` and its interaction with [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mZipArchiveThresholdInputStream.getNextEntry[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`:  [0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Inspect whether `[0m[1;35mgetNextEntry[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` can block or spin indefinitely on certain [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmalformed inputs.  [0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The performance characteristics of decompression routines invoked beneath the [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mZIP entry source.  [0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Configuration and behavior of `[0m[1;35mZipSecureFile.getMaxFileCount[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` and whether it[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreturns an expected finite value for tests.  [0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Any other code paths in `poi-ooxml` that perform ZIP entry processing [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstream skipping, `InputStream` wrappers[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m that might bypass the new entry-count [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mchecks.  [0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Test harness setup to confirm that the timeout originates inside the ZIP [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreading loop rather than upstream or downstream logic.[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Initial Issue Log[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mHere is the initial issue log of the codebase:[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<issue>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mERROR: libFuzzer: timeout[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95missue[0m[39m>[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Additional Issue Log[0m                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<additional_issue>[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m36[0m[39m: * @see ZipInputStreamZipEntrySource#[0m[1;35msetThresholdBytesForTempFiles[0m[1;39m([0m[39mint[0m[1;39m)[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m37[0m[39m: *[0m[35m/[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m38[0m[39m:public final class ZipArchiveFakeEntry extends ZipArchiveEntry implements [0m       [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m39[0m[39m:    private static final Logger LOG = [0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mPoiLogManager.getLogger[0m[1;39m([0m[39mZipArchiveFakeEntry.class[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                 [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m42[0m[39m:    [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m can be overwritten via [0m[1;35mIOUtils.setByteArrayMaxOverride[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m                  [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m45[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m46[0m[39m:    [0m[35m/[0m[39m**[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m47[0m[39m:     * Set the maximum size of a single entry in a zip-file.[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m48[0m[39m:     * @param maxEntrySize number of bytes at which a zip entry is regarded as [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtoo large for holding in memory[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m49[0m[39m:     *                     - defaults to 100_000_000 [0m[1;39m([0m[39mapprox 100Mb[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. A value of [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m-1[0m[39m means the default value is used.[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m50[0m[39m:     *[0m[35m/[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m51[0m[39m:    public static void [0m[1;35msetMaxEntrySize[0m[1;39m([0m[39mint maxEntrySize[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                       [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39magainst the Apache POI OOXML code paths. In response, a patch was applied to [0m       [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mit into the `ZipArchiveInputStream`. Despite this change, the fuzzer still reports [0m [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthat the fuzzer’s inputs are causing the code under test never to terminate or to [0m  [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The harness code [0m[1;39m([0m[39mthe fuzzer entry point[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m invokes `ZipHelper` methods but is [0m  [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `ZipHelper`: Confirm that the bounded stream is actually enforced and not [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcircumvented elsewhere.  [0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `org.apache.commons.compress.utils.BoundedInputStream`: Verify its behavior [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwhen the limit is reached [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdoes it throw, block, or return EOF?[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `ZipArchiveInputStream` and `ZipArchiveThresholdInputStream`: Check for [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minternal loops or blocking reads that may not respect the underlying stream’s EOF. [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `[0m[1;35mZipArchiveFakeEntry.getMaxEntrySize[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`: Examine the configured limit value [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand ensure it is appropriate and non-zero.  [0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Surrounding OPC [0m[35m/[0m[39m OpenXML code paths that invoke these streams, to see if [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39madditional stream wrapping or re-reading occurs outside `ZipHelper`.  [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The fuzz harness setup [0m[1;39m([0m[39minput generation, timeouts, coverage settings[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to rule[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mout misconfiguration but not as a primary cause.[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mNo speculation on root causes or proposed fixes is included; this report focuses [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msolely on documenting what was observed and where to look next.[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Initial Issue Log[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mHere is the initial issue log of the codebase:[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<issue>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe project’s fuzzing harness reported a hang [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlibFuzzer timeout[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m when processing [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcertain ZIP inputs. To address this, a patch was proposed that:[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Lowers the default maximum entry size in `ZipSecureFile` to [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m MB.[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Wraps the input streams in `ZipHelper.openZipStream` with commons-compress [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`BoundedInputStream` to cap reads by that size.[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Applies the same bounding to `ZipArchiveFakeEntry` when copying entry data to [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtemp files or encrypted streams.[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mWhen the patch was applied, the build failed in the poi-ooxml module with about [0m[1;36m21[0m[39m [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcompilation errors in `ZipHelper.java` and `ZipArchiveFakeEntry.java` complaining [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mof “not a statement” and missing semicolons—indicating that the inserted code was [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnot syntactically valid Java.[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mInitial Issue  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The fuzz target invoking the library on crafted ZIPs did not complete in time, [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39myielding `ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout`.  [0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- No ZIP entry size or read-length bounds existed, so malicious or malformed [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39marchives could trigger effectively infinite reads or deflations.[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPatch Attempt  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **ZipSecureFile.java**  [0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Changed `DEFAULT_MAX_ENTRY_SIZE` from `[0m[1;36m0xFFFFFFFF[0m[39mL` to `[0m[1;36m1024[0m[39m * [0m[1;36m1024[0m[39m` [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m1[0m[39m MB[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Left `MAX_ENTRY_SIZE = DEFAULT_MAX_ENTRY_SIZE` in place.  [0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **ZipHelper.java**  [0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Replaced the magic-checking `InputStream` with a [0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mBoundedInputStream[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mFileMagic.prepareToCheckMagic[0m[1;39m([0m[39mstream[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, [0m[1;35mgetMaxEntrySize[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.  [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Wrapped the resulting `processStream` again in a second `BoundedInputStream` [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbefore passing to `new [0m[1;35mZipArchiveInputStream[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.  [0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **ZipArchiveFakeEntry.java**  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In the branch writing to an encrypted temp stream or a plain temp file, [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwrapped the incoming `inp` in a `[0m[1;35mBoundedInputStream[0m[1;39m([0m[39minp, [0m[1;35mgetMaxEntrySize[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` before[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcalling `[0m[1;35mIOUtils.copy[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.  [0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPatch Application Result  [0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- During compilation of `poi-ooxml`, the Java compiler flagged comment lines and [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minserted line-number prefixes [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g. `[0m[1;36m190[0m[39m:`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m as code tokens.  [0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Errors such as “not a statement” and “[0m[32m';'[0m[39m expected” appear on the patched lines [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39min `ZipHelper.java` and `ZipArchiveFakeEntry.java`.  [0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- No errors were reported in unmodified parts of the code, and the rest of the [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbuild completed normally up to that module.  [0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mKey Observations  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The inserted lines carry numeric prefixes [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[1;36m190[0m[39m:`, `[0m[1;36m193[0m[39m:`, etc.[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m that are not [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mvalid Java syntax.  [0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The added `BoundedInputStream` usages lack import statements or a defined [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mgetMaxEntrySize[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` accessor in `ZipSecureFile`.  [0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- All compiler errors are localized to the newly patched files, indicating a [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msyntactic mismatch between the patch diff and the actual source layout.[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAreas for Further Investigation  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Verify that the patch diff only contains valid Java code [0m[1;39m([0m[39mremove inline line [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnumbers and ensure proper comment syntax[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Confirm existence and visibility of `[0m[1;35mZipSecureFile.getMaxEntrySize[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` and [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mrequired imports for `org.apache.commons.compress.utils.BoundedInputStream`.  [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Review the method signatures and package declarations in `ZipHelper` and [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`ZipArchiveFakeEntry` to ensure the new stream wrappers fit cleanly into the code [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mflow.  [0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Audit other ZIP-related utility classes for similar unbounded-read patterns to [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mget a full view of potential fuzzer hang points.[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
